Bit Moose is a free, open source ,Bitcoin mining assistant program. It allows miners to run under a background windows service. The package includes a GUI and console host. You can configure your miners from the GUI or modify the Settings.xml file yourself to fine tune adjustments. It was created by [BitcoinTalk](https://bitcointalk.org/) user *Awesomey* and released on October 31st, 2012. It is written in C# and is only available for Microsoft Windows-based systems.

